   AMBUSH-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ It's called ``ambush marketing,''
and it refers to advertisers' attempts to capitalize on a
sponsorship event without actually becoming sponsors. And with
official sponsorships for the Summer Olympic Games selling for
stratospheric sums, it is hardly surprising to officials at the
U.S. Olympic Committee that the Games frequently have been ambush
targets. By Bernard Stamler.
