</P>
<P>
   One ecologists' group even suggests that the Mondavi plan, which
covers ten plots, separated by garrigue, may promote biodiversity.
</P>
<P>
   The project, which depends on Mondavi obtaining a 99-year lease
on communal land, also has local political support. The Socialist
mayor of nearby Montpellier, George Fr(circumflex)eche, and his
friends in Aniane back it. Last month the Aniane town council
approved the plan.
</P>
<P>
   Moreover, Mondavi is offering to help the 232 members of the
local wine cooperative to upgrade and market their wines.
</P>
<P>
   Given that 40 percent of last year's harvest is still unsold,
and the region's wine growers have taken to the streets to protest
at foreign imports, the offer is hard to refuse.
</P>
<P>
   In other words, though the final decision rests with the
national agricultural minister, and Guibert vows to keep up a legal
challenge, the Americans may well start clearing their land by next
year.
</P>
<P>
   Like it or not, locals are resigned. ``The wine-growers of
Aniane,'' comments one, ``will end up as the workers of Mondavi.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-21-00 0341EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
