<P>
   NUTS&AMP;BOLTS-BASEMENTS _ Though rainfall has been at or below
normal this summer, there was at least one storm in early July that
left many in Ohio's Miami Valley, including me, with wet basements.
It's natural that basements are more damp than other parts of our
houses, but if you regularly get a puddle, a stream or even a lake
during a heavy rain, there are things you can do to fix it.
(Cummings, Dayton Daily News). 18.
