<P>
   SCOUTS-PROTESTS (San Francisco) _ When she retired from her
high-tech management job to raise her young son Will, Jan Tyler
never expected to find herself helping to stage a protest against
an outfit she and her family have long revered. But on Monday the
Cub Scout den mother from Mountain View, Calif., is taking to the
streets to protest the Boy Scouts of America policy of excluding
gay boys and leaders. Such protests are taking place in 35 cities
nationwide. By CAROL NESS.
</P>
<P>
   HATE-CRIME (San Francisco) _ A college student has been charged
with a hate crime after allegedly calling two men standing in front
of a Los Gatos, Calif., hair salon ``faggots'' and assaulting one
of them. The 21-year-old business economics major was charged with
battery and interference with the exercise of civil rights. He
denies the charges, saying he was the assault victim and that he
did not use the derogatory term. By SCOTT WINOKUR.
</P>
<P>
   CORRUPTION-TRIAL (Laredo, Texas) _ When is a fix not a fix?
Perhaps when it is an arreglo. As a verb, arreglar can mean to
repair, mend, tidy up, take care of, deal with, sort out. The word
or one of its derivatives is heard dozens of times on audiotapes
that federal prosecutors have entered as evidence in a public
corruption trial involving five men with close ties to be Webb
County district attorney's office. By BONNIE PFISTER.
</P>
