   LIEBERMAN-FAITH (Undated) The challenge of living a political
life within the confines of Orthodox Judaism may seem rigorous to
non-Jews, but Jewish leaders say the compromises Joseph Lieberman
faces as the Democratic vice presidential nominee won't be overly
difficult. Should he become vice president _ or president _
Lieberman won't be confronted with stark choices between his faith
and the national interest, these leaders say. By J. MICHAEL PARKER.
