forget the Ford Taurus, Honda Accord and Toyota Camry, and instead
buy a 2001 Dodge Stratus or Chrysler Sebring. DaimlerChrysler
officials say these sedans will hit the mark with consumers where
the previous-generation Dodge and Chrysler midsize sedans failed
miserably. By G. CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III.
</P>
<P>
   AIRLINE-TRAINING (San Francisco) _ Safi Nairobi claims she asked
her American Airlines flight attendant for an ice pack and got dry
ice instead, causing burns on her lower back that forced her to
spend a week in the hospital. Two weeks later, a similar incident
happened on another American flight, according to a separate
lawsuit. Nairobi's lawyer says the cases raise questions about the
airline's personnel training. By PETER HARTLAUB.
</P>
