</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-BONUSES (Undated) _ A survey by PriceWaterhouse says
that despite falling on hard times this year Internet CEOs
increased salary 9 percent and bonuses 28 percent. By Peter J.
Howe. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   SEC-BOSTON-SCI (Undated) _ SEC issues a cease and desist order
against Boston Scientific Corp. after its Japanese unit faked over
$75 million in sales during 1997 and 1998. The company had
corrected its financial after detecting the fraud and reporting it
to the SEC, which issued no fine. By Naomi Aoki. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   ANTIGENICS-AQUILA (Boston) _ Antigenics Inc., a biotechnology
company specializing in personalized cancer ``vaccines,'' agrees to
acquire Aquila Biopharmaceuticals Inc. for about $40 million. By
Naomi Aoki. 400 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GLF-PGA-COMMENT (Louisville, Ky.) _ When Tiger Woods slammed a
3-wood into the trees on the 12th hole Saturday, then three-putted
for a double-bogey, he added a slice of intrigue that had been
missing during this summer of domination. By Jim McCabe. 1000
words.z
</P>
<P>
   OLY-US-GYM (Boston) _ When all the tumbling, twisting, and
tabulating came to an end, America finally had its top dozen
Olympic gymnasts. The question now is, will there be the glint of
