<SLUG> BC-SURVIVOR-DRINKS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHAT TO SERVE AT A ``SURVIVOR'' PARTY
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By PAMELA MITCHELL 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Forget realism when it comes to stocking the bar at your
``Survivor'' party. Aside from the occasional Bud Light or glass of
champagne won in a Reward Challenge, the crusty castaways quenched
their thirst with water and whatever milk they could suck out of a
coconut.
</P>
<P>
   Treat your guests to one or more of these tropical drinks
adapted from ``The Ultimate A-to-Z Bar Guide'' by Sharon Tyler
Herbst and Ron Herbst (Broadway Books, $15). And be sure to have
plenty of miniature paper parasols on hand.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Beachcomber _ Around Day 33, Richard (a k a ``the naked guy'')
would have sold his soul (if he had one) for one of these
citrus-flavored concoctions.
</P>
<P>
   Granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons light rum
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon triple sec or Cointreau
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon fresh lime juice
</P>
<P>
   1 dash maraschino liqueur
</P>
<P>
   Lime slice
</P>
<P>
   Dip chilled glass rim in water, shake off excess water, then dip
rim into sugar. Shake liquid ingredients with ice. Strain into
glass. Garnish with lime slice.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Navy Grog _ &UR;  &LR; This rum-heavy drink honors ex-Navy Seal Rudy for
making it to the final round of play.
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons light rum
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons Jamaica rum
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons 86-proof Demerara rum
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon fresh lime juice
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon passion-fruit or guava nectar
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon unsweetened pineapple juice
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon orange juice
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon orgeat syrup
</P>
<P>
   { cup crushed ice
</P>
<P>
   Mint sprig
</P>
<P>
   Lime slice
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients except mint and lime in a blender. Cover
and process at medium speed until smooth, about 15 seconds. Pour
into chilled glass. Garnish with mint and lime. Serve with straw.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Pina Colada &UR; _  &LR; (begin ital)If you like Pina Coladas, and
getting caught in sideways-falling Malaysian rain (end ital) ...
You can't go wrong with this island classic.
</P>
<P>
   { cup unsweetened pineapple juice
</P>
<P>
   \ cup light or gold rum
</P>
<P>
   \ cup cream of coconut
</P>
<P>
   { cup crushed ice
</P>
<P>
   Pineapple spear
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients except pineapple in a blender. Cover and
process at medium speed until smooth, about 15 seconds. Pour into
chilled glass. Garnish with pineapple spear.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Mild Sea Breeze _  &LR; Every party needs a nonalcoholic offering.
</P>
<P>
   cup unsweetened grapefruit juice
</P>
<P>
   { cup cranberry juice
</P>
<P>
   Lime wedge
</P>
<P>
   Pour liquids into chilled glass two-third full of ice cubes. Mix
well. Garnish with lime wedge.
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
