<HEADLINE>
HOW TO THROW A SURVIVOR PARTY
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
The debut season of ``Survivor'' wraps Wednesday. Have you planned
your party yet?
<TEXT>
<P>
   If not, don't despair. Check out our Survivor Kit, a guide for
throwing together a proper castaway countdown bash. It includes:
</P>
<P>
   How to turn your den into Pulau Tiga, the castaways' home away
from home.
</P>
<P>
   Since pan-fried rat is so five minutes ago, try a recipe for
Squirrels a la King.
</P>
<P>
   Tips to go beyond the obvious (Gloria Gaynor's ``I Will
Survive'') when providing background music for the night.
</P>
<P>
   And, favorite recipes for tropical drinks worthy of miniature
paper parasols.
</P>
<P>
   The one true survivor, and $1 million winner, will be decided in
the two-hour finale, followed by an hourlong reunion show with all
16 castaways.
</P>
<P>
   Don't worry too much about the losers in this survival of the
feistiest contest. Each of them will receive some cash. Depending
on how long each contestant survived, the amount ranges from $2,500
for the first person kicked off the island to $100,000 to the
runner-up.
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
</TEXT>
