   NY-PESTICIDES (New York) _ New Yorkers will have a right to know
a lot more about pesticide use in local schools and neighborhoods
beginning next year under a bill signed into law on Monday by Gov.
George Pataki. But the complex and multitiered nature of the
legislation also means that its effects could be deeply uneven
around the state and even within the same community. By Kirk
