<P>
   VERIZON-STRIKE (Undated) _ In the lexicon of the high-technology
companies that are reshaping the economy, terms like stock options,
profit sharing, and overtime loom large. So it no small wonder that
the contract agreement reached by Verizon Communications and its
unions, which makes provisions on these issues and many more, has
raised eyebrows. While the direct effect is almost impossible to
gauge, the apparent consensus about the settlement between Verizon
and the Communications Workers of America and the International
Brotherhood of Electrical Workers, is that the unions came away as
winners, and perhaps, as meaningful participants in the New Economy
that was ready to leave them at its margins, according to analysts.
By Simon Romero.
</P>
